{"key":"post-12789094","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12789094</id>\n<content>The reason for not rolling in vermiculite after first flush is because in the non-sterile environment of a fruiting chamber, contaminant spores naturally land on the cakes, but they can't germinate.&amp;nbsp; However, if you protect them with a fresh layer of substrate(verm), they can easily germinate and ruin the cakes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Rinse well between flushes, soak for a few hours, and then return to fruiting conditions, but it's best not to roll in verm.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12789104</next>\n<prev>12789087</prev>\n<first>12786544</first>\n<last>12790680</last>\n<when>1277300715</when>\n<utime>06/23/10 04:45 PM</utime>\n</post>"}